text.section:
The written procedures adopted by the Joint Ethics Committee under subsection (a) of this section:
shall be available for public inspection;
shall be provided to each legislator who is the subject of a hearing;
shall authorize a legislator to:
be represented by counsel;
cross-examine witnesses; and
subject to limitations established by the Joint Ethics Committee in its written procedures, be provided an opportunity to reasonably inspect any records that the Joint Ethics Committee intends to use during the hearing; and
subject to paragraphs (1) and (2) of this subsection, may be amended by the Joint Ethics Committee at any time.
